WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.543 --> 00:00:04.796
Before a new Claude model ships,

00:00:04.796 --> 00:00:08.842
a small group of customers
is already testing it, breaking it,

00:00:08.842 --> 00:00:10.844
and shaping what ships with it.

00:00:11.511 --> 00:00:13.805
We sat down to see what they're learning.

00:00:20.395 --> 00:00:23.606
When you get something new from Anthropic, what is the energy like?

00:00:23.606 --> 00:00:25.900
We know a storm's ahead,
but there's something exciting

00:00:25.900 --> 00:00:28.486
about a storm
because it's all hands on deck.

00:00:28.486 --> 00:00:30.572
Yeah, it feels like
we're moving at the speed of light.

00:00:31.156 --> 00:00:33.867
That's like getting the call and jumping
from whatever you're working on.

00:00:33.867 --> 00:00:36.536
We have something new,
let's figure out what it's like.

00:00:36.536 --> 00:00:38.997
The moment we get
a new model from Anthropic,

00:00:38.997 --> 00:00:42.125
we realize the grounding has changed.

00:00:43.877 --> 00:00:47.422
What's it like to work at a company
that's helping to shape the frontier?

00:00:47.422 --> 00:00:48.506
It's insanely fun.

00:00:48.506 --> 00:00:50.216
All of us are just in learning mode.

00:00:50.216 --> 00:00:54.054
This moment just feels like a generational
opportunity for anyone in this industry.

00:00:54.054 --> 00:00:58.892
I feel very lucky
and also very responsible.

00:00:58.892 --> 00:01:02.854
We need to continue to push the envelope,
continue innovating, being more secure,

00:01:02.854 --> 00:01:04.773
and making things easier to build with.

00:01:04.773 --> 00:01:09.319
In a way, I love that I can unlock
a new class of developers and builders.

00:01:11.488 --> 00:01:13.740
What's the first thing
you throw at a new model?

00:01:13.740 --> 00:01:17.827
The very first thing
is we will start automated evals

00:01:17.827 --> 00:01:19.454
just so that they start
running in the background.

00:01:19.454 --> 00:01:22.457
One use case that is a
pipe dream that's easy to point to

00:01:22.457 --> 00:01:26.086
as a particularly complex legal task
is drafting an S1.

00:01:26.086 --> 00:01:29.631
Now with agentic capabilities
where these models can go out

00:01:29.631 --> 00:01:34.094
and find information that they need,
synthesize it, edit documents,

00:01:34.094 --> 00:01:38.181
we're getting to larger
and larger chunks of the S1

00:01:38.181 --> 00:01:40.892
that you can just send
the model on its way to do.

00:01:40.892 --> 00:01:43.019
Just by swapping in that one model,

00:01:43.019 --> 00:01:45.647
every question I ever wanted
to ask it started getting answered.

00:01:45.647 --> 00:01:49.234
It went from this agent can
sometimes answer questions,

00:01:49.234 --> 00:01:50.777
sometimes get stuck, to,

00:01:50.777 --> 00:01:54.114
oh, my God, it is answering
every question quickly and accurately.

00:01:54.114 --> 00:01:58.243
The dashboard of the testing agent
success rate has just increased

00:01:58.243 --> 00:02:01.496
by, I think it's 20%.

00:02:01.496 --> 00:02:04.916
Things that don't work today
are the best sign for,

00:02:04.916 --> 00:02:07.127
here's what the next models
are going to be way better at.

00:02:07.127 --> 00:02:10.004
Seeing evals that have never
worked start working

00:02:10.004 --> 00:02:11.965
and then start working consistently,

00:02:11.965 --> 00:02:13.758
this model is going
to be something special.

00:02:15.677 --> 00:02:17.637
What's it like working with Anthropic?

00:02:17.637 --> 00:02:21.141
It feels like I have a conversation
with you almost every other day.

00:02:21.141 --> 00:02:23.893
The engineers on the team, I feel like,
are almost on the same team.

00:02:23.893 --> 00:02:27.147
It's less like we're just
buying something from you,

00:02:27.147 --> 00:02:29.566
and more like we build with you.

00:02:29.566 --> 00:02:32.443
We have a very high trust bar
that anything you publish

00:02:32.443 --> 00:02:33.820
is not going to be slop.

00:02:35.321 --> 00:02:39.576
What is one word or phrase
that characterizes what it feels like

00:02:39.576 --> 00:02:40.994
to actually be building at the frontier?

00:02:40.994 --> 00:02:43.037
Dazzling, if that makes sense.

00:02:43.037 --> 00:02:44.747
It can be blinding at times.

00:02:44.747 --> 00:02:46.958
Just the brightness,
opportunity, excitement.

00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:49.169
Compounding, we get the latest tools,

00:02:49.169 --> 00:02:51.212
which leads to our customers
getting a better product,

00:02:51.212 --> 00:02:53.256
which leads to us getting better products.

00:02:53.256 --> 00:02:58.386
You have a big wave under
you that is changing

00:02:58.386 --> 00:03:02.223
the way your user is working
and changing the way you are working.

00:03:02.223 --> 00:03:04.434
And you have to keep your balance.

00:03:04.434 --> 00:03:06.227
And you know there are
bigger waves coming.

